race.comment: LOCHINVAR LORD (6) is struggling to break through but racing consistently, finishing in the minors three starts on end. Last time out flew the lids with a fast early sectional but gathered in and finished in the minors when third (22.71) at Mandurah over 400m. The form from his last run stacks up well. Expected to feature in the finish again. KAKEGURUI (4) lines up here off a comfortable win at Mandurah after jumping from box 6 (17.30). Will need some luck early after drawing a tricky box here. Can measure up again. MILKY BAR KID (2) broke a string of placings finishing in the money two on end before a last start fourth (22.32) at this track. Key runner on best form. LADY FREYA (3) is worth some thought after placing at this track and distance last start.
